#soldiers:
####################################################################################################################
# About the distribution of items and skills among the troops:
# Items: I distributed the armors according to the following rough guidelines:
#			Horses: Heavy Cavalry upgrade their horses according to: light horse -> cataphract -> Warhorse -> long warhorse / charger
#			Armor:	Cavalry: They receive the same tier armor as the tier they are (example: t5 cavalry receives t5 armor).
#					Infantry: They receive their tier minus 1 (example: t5 infantry receives t4 armor).
#					Archers: They receive their teir minus 2 (for example: t5 archers receive t3 armor).
#			Boots: Same tier as the armor they have.
#			Helmets: Same tier as the armor they have.
#			Gauntlets: I normalised them to tier 5 units. Earlier units work their way up to this tier, and later progress after it:
#					Cavalry: Tier 5 units have tier 6 gauntlets. T6 and t7 of course too. t4 has t5 gauntlets, t3 has t4 gauntlets, t2 has t2 gauntlets.
#					Infantry: Tier 5 units have tier 5 gauntlets. T6 and t7 have t6. t4 has t4 gauntlets, t3 has t2 gauntlets and t2 has none.
#					Horse Archers: Tier 5 units have tier 4 gauntlets. T6 has t5 gauntlets, t7 has t6 gauntlets. t4 has t2 gauntlets . t3 and t2 have none.
#					Archers: Tier 5 units have tier 2 gauntlets. t6 has t2 too, and t7 has t4 gauntlets. t4, t3 and t2 have none.
#			Shields: Rule of the thumb is: no shields for archers, 2 handed swordsmen and tier 1 and half of the units of tier 2. For the rest: pavise shields to archers.
#			Weapons:
#					Arrows: +1 bonus for tiers 2 till 4, +2 bonus for tiers 5 till 7.
#					Bows: There are 6 bow types, who progress with one type per tier along tiers 2 till 7.
#					Throwing: Looked at how many there were to distributed, and assigned them to one branch and divided them to progress.
#					Blunt, 2-h swords, lances, spears, axes: same idea as throwing weapons.
#					Swords: I assigned swords according to the following schedule:
#						Value	- Tier soldiers
#						50		- t1
#						100-150	- t2
#						200		- t3
#						300		- t4
#						400		- t5
#						500		- t6
#						600		- t7
# Guarantees: All soldiers in the Reworked and Expanded have their items guaranteed. In the Native tree they have the same guarantees as Native has.
#			Order: tf_guarantee_ranged|tf_mounted|tf_guarantee_horse|tf_guarantee_armor|tf_guarantee_boots|tf_guarantee_helmet|tf_guarantee_gloves|tf_guarantee_shield
#
# Skills: I gave the troops skills accoring to the following guidelines:
#			Level: The division of tiers is based upon the levels of the units. It works like this:
#						t1	= level 1 - 6
#						t2	= level 7 - 12
#						t3	= level 13 - 18
#						t4	= level 19 - 24
#						t5	= level 25 - 30
#						t6	= level 31 - 36
#						t7	= level 37 - 42
#			Proficiencies: For each level a soldier gains, he receives 15 profpoints that are distributed according to his needs. A soldier doesn't 'unlearn' proficiencies or skills as he progresses along the tree.
#					All basic tier 1 soldiers of all troop trees are level 4. To calculate the skill sets they have, I did the following:
#					- I first gave all troops 40 points in each proficiency.
#					- Then I distributed proficiencies according to the following schedule:
#						Faction:		1H		2H		Pole	Bow		XBow	Throw
#						Swadia:			+20				+30		+10
#						Vaegir:			+10				+20		+30
#						Khergit:		+20		+10				+30
#						Nord:			+30		+10								+20
#						Rhodok:			+20				+10				+30
#						Sarranid:		+30		+20				+10
#						Mercenaries:	+10				+30				+20
#						Sword Sisters:	+30		+10				+20
#					- This gave the basic proficiencies for the tier 1 units. Henceforth I looked for each unit with how many levels it increased, and adjusted the stats accoridingly. I gave a maximum of 8 points per level for the primary weapon.
#			Skills: Skills increase too as a soldier advances along the tree. I used the following schedule:
#						Starting skills:
#						Faction:		IF		PS		PT		PD		SH		AL		RD		HA
#						Swadia:					2		1				1
#						Vaegir:					1				2								1
#						Khergit:								1						1		2
#						Nord:			1				2						1
#						Rhodok:			1		1								2
#						Sarranid:						1								2		1
#						Mercenaries:	2								1		1
#						Sword Sisters:							1		2				1
#						Increase per tier. On the left is the increase dependant on the weapons the soldiers have, on the right the increase per unit type.
#										Bonuses per weapon type carried 			|	bonus movement		|	Bonuses for soldier type						|				Bonuses for faction (only if applicable)
#						Tier:			melee		Bow		XBow	Throw	Shield	|	no horse	horse	|	Cav				Inf			Arch	HoArch		|	Sw		Va		Kh		No			Rh		Sa		Me		SS
#						T1:															|						|													|							1AL, 1IF								
#						T2:				1PS			1PD		1SH		1PT		1IF		|	1AL			1RD		|	1AL,1SH			1PS			-		1HA,1RD		|
#						T3:				1IF			1PD		1IF		1PT		1SH		|	1AL			1RD		|	1RD,1IF,1PS		1IF,1SH		-		1HA,1AL		|							
#						T4:				1PS			1PD		1SH		1PT		1IF		|	1AL			1RD		|	1AL,1SH			1PS			-		1HA,1RD		|
#						T5:				1IF			1PD		1IF		1PT		1SH		|	1AL			1RD		|	1RD,1IF,1PS		1IF,1SH		-		1HA,1AL		|
#						T6:				1PS			1PD		1SH		1PT		1IF		|	1AL			1RD		|	1AL,1SH			1PS			-		1HA,1RD		|
#						T7:				1IF			1PD		1IF		1PT		1SH		|	1AL			1RD		|	1RD,1IF,1PS		1IF,1SH		-		1HA,1AL		|
#				Final upgrade bonus:	1PS			1PD		1IF		1PT		1SH		|	1AL			1RD		|	1PS				1PS					1HA			|	1PD		1PD		1HA					1SH		1PS		1AL		1RD
#						Remember, these are all just guidelines: I can always make exceptions, as I did with the Nord to balance them out.
